To explain how exciton-phonon heat flows can be controlled we recall the mechanism of adiabatic rapid passage using chirped pulses21, as illustrated in Fig. 1b. This figure shows a typical example of the evolution of the dressed-state energies as the driving frequency sweeps through the resonance. These energies are given by the eigenvalues of Ĥs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
